name: NutritionFocusedPhysicalFindingsSNOMEDCT
title: Nutrition Focused Physical Findings SNOMED CT
description: This value set is intended for use as a answer set for the LOINC: Physical finding.nutrition - 75293-1.  This LOINC is a member of the LOINC: Nutrition Assessment Panel - 75282-4.  It can be used as part of the LOINC panel or as a component of nutrition focused physical findings documented by a Registered Dietitian Nutritionist.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Nutrition related physical appearance, muscle and fat wasting, swallow function, appetite and affect which is used in a comprehensive nutrition assessment for an individual.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patient characteristics which help define nutritional inadequacies and conditions. These elements would be part of "nutrition assessment" data.),(Inclusion Criteria: SNOMED CT terms which describe physical findings which relate to nutritional status.),(Exclusion Criteria: Other terms which are considered nutrition assessment data: food/nutrition-related history, anthropometric measurements, biochemical data, medical tests, procedures or client history-are not included in this value set.)
